The advanages of prepared statements come more into play when you have to execute a query multiple times with diffrent params.

The following example will fetch all rows by `value` from 1 to 10:
```
$value = 1;
$stmt = $pdo-&gt;prepare(&quot;INSER INTO (first, second, third) VALUES (?, ?, ?);&quot;);

$rowsToInsert = [[&quot;first&quot;, &quot;second&quot;, &quot;third&quot;]];

foreach ($rowsToInsert as $row) {
  array_map($row, function($v, $i) use ($stmt) {
    $stmt-&gt;bindValue($i + 1, $v);
  });

  $stmt-&gt;execute();
}
```

Also you are free to use other php logic to bind params:

```
$params = [
 &quot;:first&quot; =&gt; $first,
 &quot;:second&quot; =&gt; $second,
 &quot;:third&quot; =&gt; $third
];

$sql = sprintf(
  &quot;INSERT INTO (first, second, third) VALUES (%s);&quot;, 
